# Things for Alfred
Interact with [Things 3](https://culturedcode.com/things/) using [Alfred](http://www.alfredapp.com/).
## Usage
* Use the keyword `todo` to show Things lists and press `↩` to explore the contained to-dos of the selected list. The following modifier keys can be used to trigger actions in lists: - `⌘ + ↩` to show the selected list in Things UI; - `⌥ + ↩` to invoke the Quick Entry window; - `⌃ + ↩` to show tags in the target list; - `fn + ↩` to empty the Trash.
* Select a to-do and press `↩` for displaying it in Things UI. The following modifier keys can be used to trigger actions in to-dos: - `⌘ + ↩` to mark a to-do as completed; - `⌥ + ↩` to mark a to-do as canceled; - `⌃ + ↩` to delete a to-do; - `fn + ↩` to empty the Trash.
* Select a project and press `⇧ + ↩` to explore the contained to-dos.
## Contribute
To report a bug or request a feature, please [create an issue](https://github.com/xilopaint/alfred-things/issues) or [submit a pull request](https://github.com/xilopaint/alfred-things/pulls).
